1
00:00:01,501 --> 00:00:03,636
Idaho has a lot of terrain

2
00:00:03,636 --> 00:00:06,339
from tall, snowy mountains
to flat, dry deserts.

3
00:00:06,639 --> 00:00:08,808
Before you leave town
to go hit the great outdoors,

4
00:00:08,808 --> 00:00:12,212
make sure you ask yourself:
Am I ready for this hike?

5
00:00:21,788 --> 00:00:25,158
Hiking can mean a lot of different
things depending on who you ask.

6
00:00:25,425 --> 00:00:28,128
It could be something simple, like walking
through the woods after dinner,

7
00:00:28,328 --> 00:00:31,097
or summiting some of 
the tallest peaks in the state.

8
00:00:31,097 --> 00:00:33,233
Make sure no matter where

9
00:00:33,233 --> 00:00:35,402
you're heading outdoors,
you go prepared for any scenario.

10
00:00:36,236 --> 00:00:38,972
The “Ten Essentials” is a list of
basic survival items

11
00:00:38,972 --> 00:00:40,540
that's been around for decades.

12
00:00:40,540 --> 00:00:43,109
And no, it's not a bunch of expensive 
gear you have to go buy.

13
00:00:43,309 --> 00:00:45,178
It's ten categories of things

14
00:00:45,178 --> 00:00:47,747
that you should pack to help
keep you safe in the backcountry.

15
00:00:48,481 --> 00:00:50,683
First things first,
you need to know where you're going.

16
00:00:50,683 --> 00:00:54,454
That can be with a paper map and a compass,
or with a GPS, or

17
00:00:54,487 --> 00:00:56,122
even directions from your phone.

18
00:00:56,122 --> 00:00:58,591
But don't rely on an internet connection
once you get out there.

19
00:00:59,359 --> 00:01:00,960
Next, you're going to want 
to dress in layers

20
00:01:00,960 --> 00:01:03,363
so that you can adapt
to the changing trail conditions.

21
00:01:03,930 --> 00:01:06,833
Sure, that extra shirt is going to be nice
in the morning when it's shady,

22
00:01:07,033 --> 00:01:09,469
but in the afternoon in the sun
you might be a little uncomfortable.

23
00:01:10,770 --> 00:01:12,372
Speaking of that afternoon sun,

24
00:01:12,372 --> 00:01:14,374
you also need something
to protect yourself from it.

25
00:01:14,674 --> 00:01:17,310
That could be sunglasses, sunscreen,
a wide brimmed hat,

26
00:01:17,577 --> 00:01:19,479
something to keep you from getting burned.

27
00:01:19,479 --> 00:01:21,748
And yes, you need to remember it
even when it's cold out

28
00:01:21,748 --> 00:01:24,150
because that white winter snow
still reflects the sun.

29
00:01:25,185 --> 00:01:27,187
On the other hand,
if things start to get dark,

30
00:01:27,187 --> 00:01:29,122
you should have a light source with you.

31
00:01:29,122 --> 00:01:31,124
A headlamp is a great hands free option

32
00:01:31,691 --> 00:01:33,760
as long as you remember
to make sure it has fresh batteries.

33
00:01:34,727 --> 00:01:37,897
Not only should you bring water
along in a bottle or a reservoir,

34
00:01:38,131 --> 00:01:41,234
some experts say you should bring
an entire day's extra with you.

35
00:01:41,701 --> 00:01:44,003
And food might seem like a no brainer,
but make sure it's something

36
00:01:44,003 --> 00:01:46,172
that will sustain your energy
throughout the day.

37
00:01:46,673 --> 00:01:50,009
The last essentials to pack
include a pocket knife or multi-tool,

38
00:01:50,376 --> 00:01:54,881
a way to start and maintain a fire,
an emergency shelter and a first aid kit.

39
00:01:55,815 --> 00:01:59,486
These categories are just recommendations
and the items in them can be tailored

40
00:01:59,486 --> 00:02:01,387
depending on how intense your hike is.

41
00:02:01,387 --> 00:02:03,089
And just like with any gear.

42
00:02:03,089 --> 00:02:05,258
It's not going to help you
if you don't know how to use it.

43
00:02:05,258 --> 00:02:07,660
So make sure you're familiar
with the kit that you pack.

44
00:02:08,628 --> 00:02:10,530
So next time you're 
headed for the great outdoors,

45
00:02:10,530 --> 00:02:12,999
make sure you pack everything
for a fun, safe hike.

46
00:02:13,766 --> 00:02:16,136
If you liked this video,
let us know by clicking the like button.

47
00:02:16,436 --> 00:02:19,806
Check out the description for links 
to our printable “Ten Essentials” checklist

48
00:02:19,806 --> 00:02:22,542
and trail recommendations
courtesy of Visit Idaho

49
00:02:22,942 --> 00:02:25,211
and leave us a comment
about your favorite places to hike.

50
00:02:25,712 --> 00:02:27,881
Subscribe to the channel
for more local content like this

51
00:02:28,047 --> 00:02:29,149
and we'll see you on the trail.
